comment: Unique identifier assigned to each H-1B case by the Department of Labor.
Current processing status of the case, such as CERTIFIED, DENIED, WITHDRAWN.
Legal name of the employer filing the H-1B application.
Type of visa classification being applied for, e.g., H-1B, H-1B1 Chile, E-3 Australian.
Job title for the position being offered under the H-1B application.
Standard Occupational Classification (SOC) title corresponding to the job.
Indicates if the position is full-time ('Y') or part-time ('N').
Proposed start date of employment under the H-1B petition.
Total number of positions requested in the application.
Indicates if this is a new employment petition (typically 1 for new, 0 otherwise).
Indicates if the petition involves a change of employer (typically 1 for change, 0 otherwise).
City location of the employer’s main office or headquarters.
State location of the employer’s main office or headquarters.
Name of the law firm or preparer submitting the H-1B application.
City where the H-1B worker will physically work.
State where the H-1B worker will physically work.
Proposed salary for the H-1B worker, typically expressed in annualized USD.
Prevailing Wage (PW) level used to determine the appropriate wage for the job, such as Level I, II, III, IV.
